@node fabs
@section @code{fabs}, @code{fabsf}---absolute value (magnitude)
@findex fabs
@findex fabsf
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <math.h>
double fabs(double @var{x});
float fabsf(float @var{x});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
@code{fabs} and @code{fabsf} calculate 
@tex
$|x|$, 
@end tex
the absolute value (magnitude) of the argument @var{x}, by direct
manipulation of the bit representation of @var{x}.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
The calculated value is returned.  No errors are detected.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{fabs} is ANSI.
@code{fabsf} is an extension.


@*
